They insists that even if I stop hooking up and all that, they will only accept me IF I find my way back into their faith. Theirs. Not mine. Depressed or not, nothing stops me from my career goals. I might even have to drop out, and I will if that's what it takes to achieve my dreams. At least from now on, no one can say the only reason I succeed one day is due to my parents. From the mind that brought you how to find h*rny people on dating apps (run two profiles, etc.)  So recently I got into a really intense relationship. Everything happened so quickly. When it was good, it was amazing, but when she picked a fight...damn it was like fireworks in the kitchen. So damn explosive. So this goes back and forward. Things are great (and wild!) and then she explodes in fits of rage. She's attractive and tbh I'm kinda seduced by the drama. A friend of mind who's training to be a therapist says she sounds "borderline" whatever that means.  Anyway we keep going off and then back together again. I get to the point where I can't take the drama any more and ask her to leave me alone. She refuses and tells me how much she wants to "work at us" etc. Real scary stuff. So OK, I give it another try. Within two days she explodes real bad. We argue as usual and she does her "I don't think I can do this..." line. So here's the twist.  Instead of getting to the point where we go back and forth and I say, "Yeah...I can't do this either. Just please leave me alone" I switch it up (coz that line doesn't work). So instead I get super clingy. I say I've never felt this way before, now I can see us growing old together, I mention love (but not saying "I love you" - too much), and I tell her all I want is her, she's so amazing, blah blah blah. I really lay it on thick.  So now she's overwhelmed and replies, "I don't think I can be who you need me to be. I have so much to work on myself and I can't commit to something this big." Such a different tone from refusing to let me leave! I ease back a little bit so's not to be suspicious and say, "You know, I really would love for us to try to work things out - you're my baby...want to grow old together, etc. But if this is what you need, I respect your decision and the guy who ends up with you is gonna be one lucky fella."  Now she's really sweet, thanking me for the compliment but she just doesn't think it's going to work. Since then, I haven't heard from her since, when she used to message ALL the time.  So the lesson? If you want out of a relationship but it's too tricky for whatever reason, don't fight the resistance. Don't attack, don't criticise. Instead, lay on your "love" really thick - like, really thick - and trust me, even the most romantic types will freak out. "You're a great guy, I'm sure you'll find someone soon." Yep, I'm going on a date with one of the friend's friends next week.  Keep this in your pocket guys. It works like a charm to help you get rid of the crazy relationship and still come out looking like the poor sweet soul in need of comforting.

I have never depended on him when it comes to my career anyway, and I told him it will be a lot harder for me to have to fund my studies at the same time but I will. And if I have to quit, I will do it at my own volition. But nothing will stop me from being an entrepreneur and run on my own steam. I told him and mum that they are selfish because they want me to become who they think I should become. And they are forcing their beliefs on me.  Dad refused to say more but clearly show his disappointment. As much as I have to stand my ground, and I am proud I did. But the thing is, whether I agree or disagree with them they are my parents. And I still love them. They probably don't love me anymore by now. Because I am not the "good girl" I thought I was. For people like them with their blind faith, they would rather see me be an average girl as long as I continue to go to church and all that. Well, at least I no longer have to pretend to still be a godly woman.  Needless to say, my relationship with them is now strained. I never come clean about what's really going on with my life all these years, because I knew all along that they won't take it too well. They might even disown me. They are good parents. Now, I am in a quandary. I cannot live my life the way they want me to, yet I don't want our bond to be strained this way. But down inside, I knew sooner or later they might find out. I just didn't want to think about it. After all, how long can I hide it from my own parents? Someone told them, and when they confronted me face to face I simply could not lie anymore. According to them, they have even seen screenshots. It could be anyone I know, anyone who's beefing with me or whatever.  They wouldn't say who, but I guess that's not important anymore. Now that everything is out of the woodwork, there is simply nowhere to hide. I will know soon enough if my dad is going to continue to pay for my studies or not, but I have to be strong because life goes on. My next session with my therapist will be in 4 days, but I guess I needed a rant to release for now.  I cried last night. For the first time ever, I have to tell my partners I wasn't feeling well and they had to discuss without me. I never missed a discussion whether on zoom on face to face, not even on my first day of period. I cried half the night, smoked countless joints. Later I will have to meet up with Mike and Chun Yang. Okay, these aren't really their real names. At this time, only my sister still cares for me. Both my parents, perhaps they need time but chances are they will not love me the way they used to anymore. I don't blame them, but I wish it doesn't have to be this way.  Maybe I don't deserve sympathy I know. I chose this life. My sexual awakening was the beginning, but instead of resisting I somehow felt like that was me all along. I am h**ny and sexually active, I never was celibate or somehow just wanted to devote my life to God and his ways. I was simply raised and conditioned to believe in it, something my parents will never understand. Perhaps, it is wrong for me to expect them to.  But hey, I guess sooner or later I will be okay. And maybe I'd have the inspiration to write more juicy stuff later? Who knows. After all, depressed or not it wouldn't make my any less horny and if anything I sense that it'd get worse. Lmao. But hopefully, I'd find something healthier or better to cope with when I see my therapist later.  So you guys, enjoy the rest of your weekend! üòäüòäüòä
